**The Issue:** When `hoverEffect === "tilt"`, no CSS class is added to the element. The code only handles `"lift"` and `"glow"` cases, but the `"tilt"` case falls through without adding any class. This means:

1. The tilt effect relies entirely on inline styles from `useSimpleCardTilt()` composable (line 90)
2. There is no CSS class rule to support the tilt effect (unlike `hover-lift` and `hover-glow` which have CSS rules at lines 154-162)
3. No CSS class is ever added for the `"tilt"` option even though it's an accepted prop value (line 11)

The CSS rules for `hover-lift:hover` and `hover-glow:hover` exist, but there's no corresponding rule for tilt, suggesting the tilt implementation is incomplete or the CSS rules were never implemented for it.

